envelope /ˈɛnvəˌləʊp, ˈɒn-/

(envelopes) 

1. N-COUNT An envelope is the rectangular paper cover in which you send a letter to someone through the mail. 信封 

2. PHRASE If someone pushes the envelope , they do something to a greater degree or in a more extreme way than it has ever been done before. 挑战极限; 突破常规 

例： There's a valuable place for fashion and design that pushes the envelope a bit. 突破点儿常规的时尚和设计有其宝贵地位。

